The paper discusses the use of cognitive radio to increase system capacity by reusing locally unused spectrum. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the concept of spectrum pooling, which is a key aspect of cognitive radio (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of water filling, which is a common optimization technique in multimedia systems (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
